<subSubSection id="4EE4653723042659BAEF1B6AFC70FA11" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="064136BC23042659BAEF1B6AFC70FA11" blockId="1.[151,1437,1407,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BAEF1B6AFEE2FA35" bold="true" box="[151,274,1407,1434]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body medium, dorsal side glabrous. Pronotum broader than elytra, with a globiform, lateral projection. Elytra without striae, each elytron with a single longitudinal costa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4EE4653723042659BABF1BD2FA67F81A" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" type="description">
<paragraph id="064136BC23042659BABF1BD2FD5FF93A" blockId="1.[151,1437,1407,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BABF1BD2FEA9FA4D" bold="true" box="[199,345,1479,1506]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BB1B1BDDFE58FA4D" box="[355,424,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Head.</emphasis>
Mouthparts prolonged into rostrum (prognathous). Antennae serrate from 4th antennomere; clypeus with anterior margin medially emarginated; labrum small, transverse. 
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BE3D1BF9FB4CF9AA" box="[1093,1212,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Pronotum.</emphasis>
broader than elytra; lateral margins diverging strongly from base in a more or less straight line to a globiform projection about ⅓ from base. 
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BAAF1821FEBDF9E1" box="[215,333,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F23042659BAAF1821FEB9F9E1" box="[215,329,1588,1614]" class="Trilobita" family="Styginidae" genus="Scutellum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Corynexochida" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Scutellum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Pentagonal, excavate on disc. 
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659B8DF1821FD05F9E1" box="[679,757,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Elytra.</emphasis>
without striae, each elytron with a single longitudinal costa. 
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BAEF184DFF13F9DE" box="[151,227,1624,1649]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Venter.</emphasis>
Prosternal process flat, without anterior prominence; legs with tibiae with a pair of short spurs at the apex. 
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BAEF1869FEFCF939" box="[151,268,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Aedeagus.</emphasis>
Strongly sclerotised; relatively wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="064136BC23042659BABF188AFA67F81A" blockId="1.[151,1437,1407,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BABF188AFE94F915" bold="true" box="[199,356,1695,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Comparison:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F23042659BB1318B5FDF5F915" authority="Pineda &amp; Koike &amp; Barros, 2019" authorityName="Pineda &amp; Koike &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2019" box="[363,517,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampygnatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BB1318B5FDF5F915" box="[363,517,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Lampygnatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="2FB957D523042659B87418B5FD82F915" box="[524,626,1696,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to the extant genera 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F23042659B9B118B5FBABF915" authorityName="Moore and Lander" authorityYear="2004" box="[969,1115,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Semiognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659B9B118B5FBABF915" box="[969,1115,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Semiognatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F23042659BEEA18B5FA6CF915" authority="" authorityName="Solier" authorityYear="1849" box="[1170,1436,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BEEA18B5FAECF915" box="[1170,1308,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Conognatha</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BF5418B5FA63F915" box="[1324,1427,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Pithiscus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having the mouthparts prolonged into rostrum and the prosternal process flat, without anterior prominence, but differs in the following ways: 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F23042659BB9F18FDFD71F8AD" authority="Pineda &amp; Koike &amp; Barros, 2019" authorityName="Pineda &amp; Koike &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2019" box="[487,641,1768,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampygnatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BB9F18FDFD71F8AD" box="[487,641,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Lampygnatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the elytra punctate-rugose, without striae; each elytron has a single longitudinal costa with a row of punctures; and the pronotum is strongly broader than elytra, laterally with distinct globiform projections. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F23042659B8651925FD5FF8E5" authorityName="Moore and Lander" authorityYear="2004" box="[541,687,1840,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Semiognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659B8651925FD5FF8E5" box="[541,687,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Semiognatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F23042659B89E1925FC00F8E5" authority="" authorityName="Solier" authorityYear="1849" box="[742,1008,1840,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pithiscus">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659B89E1925FC80F8E5" box="[742,880,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Conognatha</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659B9F91925FC18F8E5" box="[897,1000,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Pithiscus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
has the elytra punctate, with around 9 striae, each with a row of punctures and with around 10 interstriae without a rows of punctures; interstriae can be flat or convex (weakly costate) or alternate between the two, but not with just a single costa as in 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F23042659BEAA196DFA9CF83D" authority="Pineda &amp; Koike &amp; Barros, 2019" authorityName="Pineda &amp; Koike &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2019" box="[1234,1388,1912,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampygnatha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="547" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BEAA196DFA9CF83D" box="[1234,1388,1912,1938]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Lampygnatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the pronotum is narrower or only slightly broader than the elytra and with lateral margins without distinct projections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4EE465372304265ABABF19D5FAB2FF78" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="544" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="064136BC2304265ABABF19D5FAB2FF78" blockId="1.[151,1437,1407,2010]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,153,215]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="544" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE23042659BABF19D5FEA2F875" bold="true" box="[199,338,1984,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="543">Etymology:</emphasis>
The generic name is a contraction and combination of “ 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F23042659B99019AAFB85F876" box="[1000,1141,1983,2009]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lampyridae</taxonomicName>
” and the Greek adjective “ 
<emphasis id="348AEAAE2307265ABADC1E8CFEC1FF1C" box="[164,305,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="544">prognathous</emphasis>
” (having a projecting lower jaw) in reference to the resemblance of the new taxon with some species of 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F2307265ABACE1EA8FECDFF78" box="[182,317,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lampyridae</taxonomicName>
and the mouthparts prolonged into rostrum, as in the genera 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F2307265AB9901EA8FB82FF78" authorityName="Eschscholtz" authorityYear="1829" box="[1000,1138,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Conognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE2307265AB9901EA8FB82FF78" box="[1000,1138,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="544">Conognatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C1FE4D3F2307265ABED01EA8FACAFF78" authorityName="Moore and Lander" authorityYear="2004" box="[1192,1338,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Semiognatha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="348AEAAE2307265ABED01EA8FACAFF78" box="[1192,1338,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="544">Semiognatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
